      %h1 What is the Sleep Apnea Patient Centered Outcome Network?
      %p
        The Sleep Apnea Patient Centered Outcomes Network (SAPCON) is the formal network name for MyApnea.Org. It is
        Sleep Apnea Association and the Division of Sleep and Circadian Disorders at Brigham and Women’s Hospital,
        the guidance of principal investigator Susan Redline, M.D., M.P.H. The MyApnea.Org network is part of a historic
        will ultimately enlist one hundred million people to provide personal health data and to guide the course of
        multiple, serious and chronic diseases. Funded by the Patient Centered Outcomes Research Institute (PCORI),
        18 Patient Powered Research Networks (PPRN) that will comprise a national “network of networks” dedicated to
        effectiveness research. It is an unprecedented effort that will redefine how health research is done in this country
        for people who suffer from these conditions each day.
