    #ASAA.col-md-12
      %h1 American Sleep Apnea Association
      http://www.sleepapnea.org/
      %p
        The American Sleep Apnea Association, founded in 1990, is a 501(c)(3)
        nonprofit organization that promotes awareness
        of sleep apnea, works for continuing improvements in treatments for this
        serious disease, and for the interests of sleep apnea patients. Its mission
        is to reduce injury, disability and death from sleep apnea and to enhance
        the wellbeing of those affected by this common disorder. The ASAA
        promotes education and awareness, coordinates and services the
        A.W.A.K.E. Network of voluntary mutual support groups,  promotes research
        and continuous improvement of care.
      %p
        The Association's governing board of directors includes both health care professionals
        and patients and patient advocates among its members. ASAA policy, however, requires
        that a majority of the directors always be patients and their advocates. The bylaws also require
        that the chair of the board be a patient or patient advocate to ensure that the ASAA would always be a
        patient-driven organization.
      .divider-light
    / col-md-9
